      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;visit&#34;&gt;Visit&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;👉 &lt;a href=&#34;https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12187-021-09880-7&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Publication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;./imagen1.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;image info&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This research was chosen as the best work in the research category in the XVIII Edition of &amp;ldquo;Premio por la Nutrición Infantil 2021 de la Fundación Éxito&amp;rdquo;. This work was leadered by the research group &amp;ldquo;Economía, Gestión y Salud (ECGESA)&amp;rdquo; of the Pontificia Universidad Javeriana Cali, in addition to Economics School of Universidad Sergio Arboleda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Éxito Foundation pointed out that the research &amp;ldquo;also contributes to our national cause, with which it is expected that in 2025 the first generation will be born with zero malnutrition and that by 2030 no child under 5 years of age will have chronic malnutrition in the country.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A pleasure to work with this team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
